{
  "texts": [
    "High availability is usually provided by commercial SIEMs such as IBM QRadar using an arranged configuration between two cooperating appliances that use mirrored links to pass all traffic between them.",
    "This ensures that all of the traffic on the network is monitored by both the appliances and the state is maintained.",
    "In the case of the open source SIEMs, Wazuh and Elastic Security have a high availability deployment option that provides good fault tolerance.",
    "OSSIM and SIEMonster community edition does not provide high availability.",
    "SIEM systems collect a huge amount of data from diverse sources and proper data visualization methods are necessary for the analysis of security events."
  ]
}